The article discusses the upcoming Summit for Democracy, which is the second of its kind. The summit aims to address the future of democracy and promote democratic resilience, human rights, and the fight against corruption. The U.S. government will invest up to $690 million in the Presidential Initiative for Democratic Renewal, which includes funding for programs such as supporting free and independent media, combating corruption, and defending free and fair elections. The summit will also focus on technology and its impact on democracy, with announcements expected on countering the misuse of technology and promoting technology for democracy. Various events have already taken place leading up to the summit, including civil society events and thematically focused events in Washington. The summit will feature world leaders and pro-democracy advocates, and discussions will continue in various locations around the world after the summit concludes. Taiwan has been invited to participate in the summit, and Ukraine's fight for democracy is also a significant part of the discussions.